						               													<description>This entry is for the Korean version of BattleCON which includes&amp;nbsp;BattleCON: Devastation of Indines,&amp;nbsp;BattleCON: Trials of Indines, BattleCON: Wanderers of Indines, and other promos packaged inside the box.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;About the game:&amp;#10;BattleCON&amp;nbsp;is a head-to-head battle card game that simulates the action and tactics of a one-on-one duel. Each player chooses one fighter from among a vast, diverse cast, and does battle against an opponent's fighter.&amp;nbsp;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each fighter has their own selection of cards which are unique to them, as well as a pool of cards which are shared among all fighters. By linking their unique&amp;nbsp;styles&amp;nbsp;to the standardized&amp;nbsp;bases, fighters can form original moves with many different interactions.&amp;nbsp;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Fighters also possess&amp;nbsp;Unique Abilities&amp;nbsp;(or UAs) which are new sub-systems that interact with their abilities. One fighter uses elemental stances, while another can charge powerful spells over time. One fighter sets up environment effects on the board, while another might control drones which attack at range.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
